Job Description

Ubisoft Montreal is looking for a Data Scientist to join its Talent & Culture team and work on people analytics projects for the studio.

On being a data scientist at Ubi Montreal

The Data Scientist must develop and execute statistical and mathematical solutions to resolve corporate and / or project challenges. The incumbent provides solutions that make processes and systems smarter by designing predictive models and must create relevant analytical methods to evaluate results in a scientific manner.

The daily life of a data scientist at Ubi Montreal

Identify issues and determine approaches and quantitative methods to develop solutions;
Develop tools to solve complex problems;
Demonstrate analytical rigor and use statistical methods to analyze large amounts of data and develop workable analyzes that apply advanced statistical techniques, such as predictive models, segmentation analysis, design and survey analysis and data mining;
Design and manage proof of concept for forecast / prescription and AI projects;
Document and define projects including data collection and processing, advanced approaches, final algorithm, detailed results and analytical criteria;
Develop material that serves to explain project findings and solve complex problems in an ingenious and effective way;
Collaborate with colleagues and managers internally and externally to share relevant complex information;
Work on short and medium term tasks that often require independence of judgment beyond the procedures in place;
Contribute to the identification of approaches and the development of new or improved technical tools.

Qualifications

What it takes to make it

Master's degree and / or doctorate in mathematics, statistics, machine learning or equivalent experience;
Minimum of 5 years of complex experience and in-depth expertise related to the position;
Ability to use and develop proven machine learning algorithms and related methods;
Ability to use advanced data science techniques ;
Ability to use statistics to understand the behavior of systems and individuals;
Ability to configure, use and develop data management systems;
Knowledge of big data technologies (Hadoop, Casandra, MongoDB, ElasticSearch);
Software Engineering Skills;
Knowledge of distributed computing to ensure model learning;
Being passionate about using the science of data in problem solving;
Ability to assess problems quickly, both qualitatively and quantitatively;
Team spirit and excellent organizational, relational and communication skills;
Bilingualism (French-English)

About us
At Ubisoft Montreal, a preeminent developer of video games located in Montreal’s dynamic Mile-End neighbourhood since 1997, we offer a work environment unique in the industry for allowing you to build and cultivate games that are part of critically acclaimed, iconic AAA franchises of international repute.
When you join Ubi Montreal, you enter a community of passionate, extraordinary developers connected by their need to innovate, to be creative and to work with the latest technology. You’ll discover a world where employees enjoy constant career advancement, a supportive learning environment, and competitive compensation packages.
More than anything, at Ubi Montreal, you will regularly ship a variety of big, quality titles – Assassin’s Creed, Far Cry, Rainbow Six, Watch_Dogs, For Honor and… well we can’t disclose all our secrets just yet… – and work with some of the most talented people in the industry.
Additional Information

null

Reporting directly to the Director of Data Science, this role is pivotal in implementing advanced time series solutions to deliver high quality results to clients.

You will be interacting with multi-function teams, including data integration, model development and other consulting functions to implement best practice and thought leadership.

This role also works very closely with client project sponsors to ensure client satisfaction and business requirement fulfillment.

Duties and Responsibilities

Implement currently available time series forecasting models
Develop customized forecasting algorithms required by specifications of each project
Prototype, simulate and benchmark accuracy of algorithms
Develops production-ready codes in R
Works with main stakeholders including but not limited to: Account Executives, Management, Project Managers and Consulting Teams
Performs various other duties as delegated or assigned.

Required Knowledge, Skills, and Experience
The successful incumbent will have:
Graduate degree in a Statistics, Math Computer Science or Engineering program;
Proficient in time series analysis and forecasting
Fundamental knowledge of supervised and unsupervised Machine Learning
Experience with data preprocessing, anomaly/outlier detection
Advanced programming skills in R language is mandatory;
Knowledge of pharmaceutical industry is an asset;
Capability to adapt in fast changing environment and eager to learn
The ability to travel and work outside regular business hours as required;
Proven, motivated self-starter with the ability to lead by example and approach and solve business problems;
Experience working in cross-functional teams with the agility to learn new software applications and technologies;
Demonstrated time management, problem solving and decision making competencies;
Ability to work autonomously and in teams to effectively prioritize multiple projects and associated deliverables;
Proven excellent communication, including presentation, hands on analytical with business savviness and customer relationship abilities;
Proven ability to comprehend, analyze and research problems of a complex nature, make decisions and/or present recommendations;

Preference for fast paced, rapid start-up culture demonstrating the values of results, teamwork, energy, agility, respect, and can-do environment

Company Description

At Ubisoft Montreal, a preeminent developer of video games located in Montreal’s dynamic Mile-End neighbourhood since 1997, we offer a work environment unique in the industry for allowing you to build and cultivate games that are part of critically acclaimed, iconic AAA franchises of international repute.
When you join Ubi Montreal, you enter a community of passionate, extraordinary developers connected by their need to innovate, to be creative and to work with the latest technology. You’ll discover a world where employees enjoy constant career advancement, a supportive learning environment, and competitive compensation packages.

Job Description

Ubisoft Enterprise Data is responsible for providing various internal services such as a data lake, enterprise data warehouse, Big Data platform and reporting tools. The Advanced Analytics & Data Science team within Enterprise Data aims to provide Data Science and Analytics oriented solutions to the various internal partner teams. As a Data Scientist within this team, you will be in charge of working on different data science topics related to the security and risk management.
Responsibilities:
Understand the problems or issues that the security and risk management team may encounter (fraud, hacking, ...) and propose solutions and relevant analyses (whether exploratory, descriptive or predictive);
Develop, automate and maintain those analyses;
Ensure collaboration with the various teams involved.

Qualifications

Education:
Bachelor's degree in Computer Science.
Relevant experience:
3-5 years experience in a similar role;
Experience in security and/or fraud data analysis an asset.
 Skills and Competencies:
Experience on use cases based on large volumes of data (SQL, Hive/Spark SQL, Impala);
Good experience with Machine Learning techniques (supervised and unsupervised: clustering, recommendation system, text mining, graph mining, NLP);
Good mathematical understanding of the different algorithms of Machine Learning;
Experience with containers (Docker, Kubernetes) and good knowledge of an ETL (Airflow or other);
Good knowledge of development practices (Git, CI/CD);
Advanced knowledge of Python programming;
Good experience with Spark and parallel programming;
Experience in data visualization (Python libraries, Tableau Software and d3.js);
Good communication skills;
Bilingual (French/English) is required both orally and written.
Additional Information

Skills and competencies show up in different forms and can be based on different experiences, that's why we strongly encourage you to apply even though you may not have all the requirements listed above.
At Ubisoft, you can come as you are. We embrace diversity in all its forms. We’re committed to fostering a work environment that is inclusive and respectful of all differences.

Senior Data Analyst- Internal Audit-MON17446

Description

BOMBARDIER

At Bombardier, our employees work together to evolve mobility worldwide - one good idea at a time. If you have a good idea, we’ll provide the environment where it will thrive and grow into a great product or customer experience. Your ideas are our fuel.

In your role, you will:

Develop, improve and implement the department’s data analysis roadmap;

Identify and subsequently act on opportunities to analyze and visualize data at every phase of the audit process;

Identify relevant data for current and future needs; coordinate data extraction and updates in the source systems;

Expertly contribute to audit and advisory engagements by putting forward and executing data analysis scripts designed to increase the quality and efficiency of audits, in accordance with latest industry standards and changing practices;

Analyze and interpret outcomes of data analysis scripts; review outcomes with managers of audited units and make recommendations;

Develop data visualization reports (e.g. Power BI) to present information in a credible, compelling way;

Help with other team tasks, as requested.

Qualifications

As our ideal candidate,

You have 5 to 10 years of experience in internal auditing and/or business intelligence;

You have a Bachelor’s degree in IT, business administration, management, accounting or a related field; Masters is an asset

You have advanced knowledge of Excel, and data analysis and visualization tools (e.g.Power BI);

You have advanced knowledge of SQL, ACL, Alteryx;

You have experience in developing/implementing a data analysis program within an internal audit team;

You have knowledge of SAP, Concur, Salesforce systems;

You have a CPA, CIA, CISA or CFE designation, an asset;

You have a solid understanding of industry best practices, especially those related to data modelling and standardization;

You have a keen sense of initiative, agility and adaptability in a constantly changing environment;

You have an analytical mindset with a talent for solving complex problems and formulating recommendations;

You have an in-depth knowledge of Microsoft Office 365 tools (SharePoint, OneDrive, OneNote, Teams);

You have a curiosity and business sense;

You have an excellent written and spoken French and English;

You have a team player with strong interpersonal skills;

You have the ability to influence others and win their support;

You are meticulous, organized and self-motivated;

You are available to travel up to 15% of the time.

